properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 7 at 9:45PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
Recent high-resolution model simulations are showing the
potential for stronger winds along the higher terrain of the
Eastern Sierra. This also includes wind prone areas of US Highway
395 south of Conway Summit tonight through early Wednesday
morning.

Southwest winds 25-35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph are
expected. Wind prone areas could see gusts as high as 60 mph.
Ridges could see gusts to 100 mph at times.

Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Travel may
become hazardous for high-profile vehicles, especially along wind
prone areas of US Highway 395. Use extra caution or postpone
travel from Conway Summit south to the Mono County line until the
winds decrease.

NWSheadline: Strong Winds Possible Into Early Wednesday Morning Along the Eastern Sierra
